                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1568-06-01" notAfter="1700"><p>Bound in an Ottoman-style, full, tight-backed, highly-polished dark brown goatskin <material>leather</material> with a flap (type II binding per Déroche). Spine later rebacked and fore-edge flap reattached with dark brown goatskin <material>leather</material>, with naturally-coloured sheepskin <material>leather</material> added to line the interior of the latter.</p>
                        <decoNote type="binding"><p>
                           Blind stamped with a scalloped central mandorla medallion with floral scrollwork in centres of the boards, and a similarly-decorated smaller medallion on the flap. 
                           Thick-and-thin fillet marginal lines on the perimeters of the boards. Endpapers of modern <material>mould-made laid paper</material> added when restored.</p></decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                           <height>192</height>
                           <width>130</width>
                           <depth>15</depth>
                        </dimensions></p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
